						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is in the <hi rend="italic">vaṭṭeḻuttu</hi> script. It records a gift of 26 cows for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirukkuṟṟālattu-Perumāḷ by <hi rend="bold">Ādittaṉ Mūvēnda-Palla[varaiyaṉ]</hi> of Āṟṟūr in Tiruppanaṅgāṭṭu-nāḍu in Śōḻanāḍu. This is assignable to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
